Looks like some of our tests use Mono.Cecil.dll built by sources from `external/Java.Interop/external/mono` instead of `external/mono/external/cecil`.

@grendello run into a test failures https://jenkins.mono-project.com/job/xamarin-android-pr-pipeline-release/1021/ which are probably result of the https://github.com/mono/cecil/commit/dbd29fa195a52b514f719d558c9a9fb29ab750cb fix missing.

Indeed the `bin/TestDebug/MSBuildDeviceIntegration/Mono.Cecil.dll` contains even older version of that method:
```
using System.Text;

private string ReadUTF8String ()
{
    if (buffer [position] == 255) {
        position++;
        return null;
    }
    int num = (int)ReadCompressedUInt32 ();
    if (num != 0) {
        string @string = Encoding.UTF8.GetString (buffer, position, (buffer [position + num - 1] == 0) ? (num - 1) : num);
        position += num;
        return @string;
    }
    return string.Empty;
}
```

